						<summary>

						<p>On pillar No. 5 in the compound of the Taluk office.</p>						

						<p>The record is dated Śaka 11 • ., <hi rend="italic">Makara-saṅkrānti.</hi></p>						

						<p>Damaged. Seems to record a gift of sheep for the supply of a prescribed quantity of ghee for a perpetual lamp in the temple of Bhīmēśvaradēva lying to the east of Dendulūru, by Māviṇṭi Mallapa.</p>						

